'''Aulendil''' was the second son and third child of [[Vardamir|Vardamir Nólimon]], the heir of [[Elros|Elros Tar-Minyatur]], first [[King of Númenor]]. His older brother took up the [[Sceptre]] as [[Tar-Amandil]]. Though he left descendants, nothing of their lives was recorded.<ref>{{UT|earlier}}</ref>

==Etymology==
''Aulendil'' is a [[Quenya]] name, meaning "Servant of [[Aulë]]" according to [[Christopher Tolkien]].<ref>{{UT|Index}}, entry "Aulendil"</ref> Paul Strack explains that according to ordinary nomenclature, it should mean "Friend of Aulë", because of the suffix ''[[-ndil|-(n)dil]]'' ("friend", "lover", "devoted to").<ref>{{webcite|author=Paul Strack|articleurl=https://www.eldamo.org/content/words/word-453608467.html|articlename=Q. ''Aulendil'' m.|website=Eldamo|accessed=20 January 2022}}</ref>

